# Dynamically updating the sample application



## Passing in configuration values 

This shows how to connect to the postgresql container, pass in the environment variable, and have that update the rails app container.

    docker-compose exec railsapp sh -c "echo -n 'secret_key_base=\"$(rails secret)\"' | hab apply --peer db myrailsapp.default $(date +%s)"

### Add in the appropriate database info to get railsapp to connect to db:

    docker-compose exec db su -c ./db_create.sh

